(Photo: WFMY News 2 Sports) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Due to the threat of inclement weather on Saturday, Oct. 3, the North Carolina A&T football game scheduled for 2 p.m., against Hampton at Armstrong Stadium in Hampton, Va., has been moved to a noon start on Saturday, Oct. 3. 
The Aggies (2-1, 0-0 MEAC) will be heading into their conference opener while the Pirates are 2-2 overall and 1-1 in the MEAC. Read or Share this story: http://on.wfmy.com/1RkNlkK TOP VIDEOS
